-- Encapsulation
-- Encapsulation is the practice of hiding the
data of an object and if user wants to access the data (CREATE,UPDATE,READ,DELETE)
they have to used the public methods Which Getters and Setters


-- why it is used?
-- validation : You can prevent "grabage" data from entering your object

-- Prevent access and manage access
read-only Access: you can provide a getter but not setter,
making a field "read-only".

Data masking: you can change how data is stored internally without
changing how the user see it.

